gunmen firing from a passing car wounded two 
british soldiers in west germany late friday night the defense 
ministry in london reported 
no group asserted responsibility for the attack in muenster 
northwest germany but the ministry suspected members of the irish 
republican army 
the outlawed ira has attacked british troops stationed in west 
germany in recent years extending its guerrilla warfare from 
northern ireland 
a ministry statement said the soldiers were offduty and wearing 
plain clothes when they were shot at as they walked toward their 
barracks at 11 pm the soldiers were hospitalized but their 
condition was not given 
the muenster barracks is headquarters of the british armys 4th 
armored brigade in west germany 
west german authorities this week intensified their search for 
ira guerrillas believed operating there after a monday bombing 
attempt on a british military housing area in hanover a british 
soldier spotted the bomb under his car and it was safely defused 
the federal criminal office in wiesbaden west germanys national 
investigative body said tuesday that investigators were looking for 
apartments and weapons caches used by the irish guerrillas 
it said the bomb found in hanover is believed to have come from 
an ira cache in west germany it was the third irarelated bomb 
incident at a british military post in northern germany this summer 
on july 2 a bomb killed a british soldier as he was getting into 
his car in a hanover residential area housing many british military 
families 
a bomb exploded in the living quarters at a british barracks near 
osnabrueck on june 19 but no one was injured 
the mainly roman catholic ira is fighting to unite northern 
ireland a british province where protestants outnumber catholics 
32 with the predominantly catholic republic of ireland under 
socialist rule 
