<TEXT>
seymour krim an author and critic who edited an 
anthology of writings of the beat generation has died at age 67 
krim had been suffering from heart disease for some time he was 
found dead wednesday in an apparent suicide at his home said 
officer janice swinney a police spokeswoman 
a reporter for the herald tribune from 1965 to 1966 he 
contributed reviews and articles to many publications including the 
new york times book review 
he wrote an introduction to jack kerouacs desolation angels 
a novel published in 1965 and edited manhattan stories of a 
great city 1954 and the beats 1960 an anthology of the 
beat generation he also published three collections of essays 
survivors include a sister blanche levie of newport ri and a 
brother norman of boston 
</TEXT>
