been ambiguous about the reasons for not being represented 
us ambassador arthur davis a political appointee left panama 
in may and president bush said friday that there are no plans to 
send him back 
bush said no diplomatic contacts are planned with the new 
government headed by president francisco rodriguez a friend of 
noriega since high school who served as government comptroller for 
seven years noriega will continue to serve as the behindthescenes 
power in panama 
among the larger latin american democracies only mexico and 
ecuador have ambassadors in panama officials said among those not 
represented at that level are venezuela peru uruguay colombia 
brazil chile and argentina 
the officials insisting on anonymity left open the possibility 
that the recall of one or more of the ambassadors from these 
countries was unrelated to political developments in panama 
the administration on friday used the occasion of the appointment 
