the area of the clash 
the clash occurred before dawn near the village of beit yahun 
six miles northwest of the israeli border said an israeli army 
spokesman who requested anonymity in line with military regulations 
the spokesman said the dead gunman carried a sovietmade ak47 
assault rifle and large amounts of ammunition and plastic explosives 
later soldiers showed reporters the body of the dead guerrilla 
who was wearing a camouflage uniform the soldiers also showed three 
kalashnikov assault guns two of which apparently belonged to the 
escaped fighters 
israel created the security zone in 1985 as a buffer area after 
withdrawing the bulk of its force following a threeyear occupation 
