decision to fly an airplane load of people into a thunderstorm 
delta argued in the 14month trial that government meteorologists 
and air traffic controllers failed to warn the crew of the severity 
of the weather the national transportation safety board ruled that 
the crash was caused by wind shear a dangerous downdraft of air 
associated with severe thunderstorms 
delta already has paid 66 million in damages as a result of the 
case in those cases the plaintiffs waived the liability issue 
sixteen families are continuing to sue delta over the crash 
the government did not escape criticism in belews ruling which 
cited the responses of controllers and meteorologists 
belew said tower personnel should have made sure that incoming 
pilots were aware of weather conditions and that a meteorologist 
should have been sure that the weather was being monitored 
continuously while he took a long dinner break 
but belew cited other cases in which the controllers failure to 
warn pilots of bad weather was not characterized as negligence 
james dillman attorney for the federal aviation administration 
said the controllers would be briefed on the ruling but that no 
formal disciplinary action will be taken 
in washington joe friday assistant administrator for weather 
services at the national oceanic and atmospheric administration 
said we are continuing to work with the faa and the aviation 
industry to improve our science and technology so that this kind of 
tragedy will not be repeated 
belew discounted the government contention that delta had not 
adequately trained pilots to handle wind shear situations he called 
deltas training lax but not a factor in the accident 
the judge also ruled out the possibility that tranquilizers capt 
edward m connors might have been taking at the time of the accident 
contributed to the crash 
pilot error also was cited as a cause of a delta crash in 1988 
which killed 14 people the airline has accepted responsibility for 
that crash and fired the flight crew after it was determined that 
the flaps were not set in the proper position for takeoff 
