that can be handed down by police without a court appearance 
pan said the law requires that police notify families within 24 
hours of detention and sets a sevenday limit for holding suspects 
without charging them but the new yorkbased international league 
for human rights reported to the united nations that these rights 
are often being waived for the recent prodemoncracy protesters 
