his death came five months after he ascended from the top post at 
the national league to become baseball commissioner and eight days 
after he banned pete rose baseballs alltime hit leader for 
betting on the game 
fay vincent deputy commissioner was named acting commissioner 
saturday 
giamatti was found unconscious in his bed and in full cardiac 
arrest when officers responding to a call from one of his sons 
arrived at 3 pm he was pronounced dead about an hour and a half 
later said matthew stackpole of marthas vineyard hospital 
edgartown police said giamattis wife toni and his son who 
were with him when he died left the island in the middle of the 
night to return to their hamden conn home 
giamattis body was taken by boat saturday from the island to 
falmouth hospital the body was then driven to connecticut 
according to hospital spokeswoman kathy regis 
friends had earlier suggested that the rose affair had taken a 
toll on giamatti a chainsmoker who called cigarettes his primary 
vice 
but in an aug 18 interview with the associated press giamatti 
brushed aside the notion that we was overstressed by the rose matter 
funeral services and burial will be private according to beecher 
amp bennett inc a hamden conn funeral home a memorial service 
will be held later 
the commissioners death elicited a flood of testimonials from 
the worlds of baseball and higher education for the versatile man 
who made his mark both as a renowned renaissance scholar and a 
tough worldwise administrator 
at fenway park the home of giamattis beloved boston red sox 
the flag was lowered to halfstaff before a contest with the seattle 
mariners after word of his death reached the park 
roger angell a noted baseball historian and writer held 
giamatti in high esteem 
he was just beginning to make his contribution to baseball he 
was prepared to take the game into the future he cared about its 
history and values angell said the night of giamattis death 
he was like no other figure in sports that i can think of 
president bush a fellow alumnus of yale where giamatti was 
president from 1978 to 1986 said the two were close friends and had 
talked at length about the rose case and all through that i was 
thinking of the difficulty that he had in setting these standards 
that high and staying with it 
former secretary of state cyrus vance a longtime friend of 
giamatti and one of his neighbors on marthas vineyard called the 
death tragic 
he was a dear friend and a human being whom i greatly loved and 
admired said vance a yale graduate who also served on the 
universitys board of trustees 
on saturday an executive council of baseball club owners 
appointed vincent acting commissioner baseball officials have said 
vincent a 50yearold former chief executive officer of columbia 
pictures is the leading candidate to succeed giamatti 
fay vincent is a wonderful man said new york yankees owner 
george steinbrenner 
born in boston on april 4 1938 giamatti was only 40 when he 
became yales youngest president in 200 years he had joined the 
yale faculty in 1966 after teaching italian and comparative 
literature at princeton university 
giamatti is survived by his wife and three children marcus 
bartlett paul edward valentine and elena walton giamatti 
