passenger fares on chinese trains planes and 
ships will roughly double as of tuesday providing additional funds 
for the crowded transportation system and new burdens for 
inflationhit users 
government spokesman yuan mu in an announcement reported in the 
official press sunday said the price increases will pay for 
renovations and expansion of the transportation system 
yuan said train tickets will go up from the equivalent of a half 
cent per person per kilometer 062 us miles to at least one cent 
a lowerclass sleeping berth from beijing to canton 1200 miles 
to the south has cost the equivalent of 16 a factory worker 
receives an average 27 per month 
yuan said prices will increase by 77 percent for domestic air 
flights but airline fares for foreigners will remain unchanged this 
year 
