raised to be a gracious hostess and 
housewife violeta barrios de chamorro has been thrust upon the 
political stage to play a leading role in turbulent nicaragua 
she was selected saturday as the presidential candidate of a 
14party opposition coalition for the feb 25 general election 
dona violeta as she is called by supporters and enemies is a 
strong prodemocracy figure and her lack of formal political 
affiliation makes her a unifying symbol for the national opposition 
union coalition members range from communist to conservative 
parties 
mrs chamorros life resembles that of president corazon aquino 
of the philippines both women come from wealthy families married 
politically ambitious men and embarked on what they thought would be 
a behindthescenes life 
both became widows their husbands felled by assassins both 
picked up their husbands political torches and continued the work 
with very little preparation experience or ambition of their own 
