<TEXT>
confusion corner is the nickname for 
the only trafficlight intersection in town 
it could describe most parts of this 25yearold community as 
federal banking regulators begin seeking a buyer for the development 
company that owns more than 10 percent of the towns land and nearly 
all of the major recreation and public facilities 
residents are looking for reassurances that life will continue as 
always amid the sprinklerfed lawns and bicycles leaning unlocked 
against evenly spaced palms on the western edge of the everglades 
the one thing i keep repeating is dont worry nothing is 
going to change but as soon as they hear the federal government is 
involved they panic said carl strunk president of land resources 
corp which came under federal control in may 
land resources is among the more curious jetsam of the nations 
savings and loan crisis which has coughed up other odd thrift 
institution holdings from llamas to a desert bordello 
land resources was acquired in 1984 by security savings and loan 
of scottsdale ariz which previously owned a 64 percent stake and 
paid off the companys 100 million debt to citicorp when the 
thrift was declared insolvent this year regulators seized its 
assets 
its strange for sure said william crocker appointed by the 
federal deposit insurance corp to oversee security savings which 
had about 1 billion in assets many sampls had real estate but to 
own part of a town is really unusual 
this past week crocker said 60 to 80 information packets would 
be sent to potential bidders around the world the rundown of whats 
for sale includes 29000 home lots two 18hole golf courses a 
1700seat auditorium a building supply store a weekly newspaper 
and a 121room hotel with a restaurant 
although land resources has sold many of its former holdings 
including two shopping centers and a bowling alley it remains the 
largest employer of the towns 25000 residents 
crocker said financially qualified bidders will be given tours of 
lehigh acres later this month bids accompanied by a 250000 
deposit should be reviewed in november and a deal completed before 
christmas he said 
crocker would not name parties that already have expressed 
interest and said only that the property is valued in the eight 
figures 
this spring miamibased general development corp offered about 
625 million for land resources which also has smaller real estate 
holdings in the central florida towns of sebring and interlachen 
but the fdic called off the sale 
strunk predicts land resources which had about 45 million in 
revenue last year will be purchased by an established development 
firm interested in maintaining operations rather its breakup value 
im convinced the whole of this company is worth more than the 
sum of its parts said strunk 
lehigh acres like much of the everglades fringelands was 
part of a large cattle ranch network before the postwar development 
boom in 1954 about 60500 acres of the lucky lee ranch was 
purchased to create a new town in lee county named for confederate 
gen robert e lee land resources acquired the property in 1968 
original plans were for a retirement haven for northern workers 
in one section targeted for extelephone employees the streets bear 
names such as switchboard and long lines 
although nearly 90 percent of the lots are deeded there are few 
buildings outside the main roadways only blue road signs stand on 
the many overgrown gridpattern streets stretching into scrubpalm 
brush 
but other sections of lehigh acres are typical smalltown 
america churches banks a small hospital two chinese restaurants 
and a struggling industrial park 
doing some theoretical calculation strunk said lehigh acres has 
the potential for about 400000 residents if everyone came down to 
build on the lots they own 
thats a long way away he admitted lehigh acres is presently 
growing by about 1000 residents annually and land resources still 
brings families down for subsidized vacations to tour the community 
and timeshare units less than half the residents now are retirees 
with the others mostly commuting to fort myers about 12 miles 
northeast said strunk 
were just like any small town anywhere he said it just 
happens that a failed sampl owned part of it 
but word of the federal takeover is a tender subject 
in july strunk wrote a frontpage article in the companyowned 
lehigh times newspaper in an attempt to soothe local apprehension 
about the sale strunk also has discouraged the nearly 500 land 
resources employees from discussing the pending sale with reporters 
this place is mr and mrs middle america its dayton ohio 
and detroit mich they are going to spend a lot of time worrying 
about this if people keep sounding alarmed said strunk i keep 
saying its not a big deal 
he may be right at the kmart lunch counter residents seemed 
more concerned with gossip than speculation on the fate of land 
resources 
this town will survive said joseph ferrante a retired new 
york police officer at worst maybe a new owner over there will 
be good it could be a change for the better 
</TEXT>
