<TEXT>
as summer draws to a close over labor day 
weekend many conversations at cookouts and cocktail parties likely 
will turn to what the stock markets recordsetting august means for 
september and beyond 
unlike past years when trading often was becalmed in the summer 
with investors taking holidays away from wall street the past month 
earned a place in the history books 
most notably the dow jones average of 30 industrials finally 
achieved what several other closely watched stock performance 
measures already had accomplished reaching an alltime high after 
setting many postcrash highs 
on aug 24 the dow average made its first move into uncharted 
territory since before the oct 19 1987 crash with a 5653point 
surge to 273464 it extended the advance the last week in the 
month reaching 274336 on aug 28 the previous record of 272242 
had stood since aug 25 1987 
broader indicators turned in comparable performances the new 
york stock exchanges composite index of all listed common stocks 
repeatedly hit new highs in august as did standard amp poors 
500stock composite index 
stock buyers were motivated partly by hopes of profiting from 
acquisitions or takeover attempts much of the thrust behind the 
markets move came from airlines for instance 
ual corp soared when news surfaced that los angeles investor 
marvin davis was seeking the parent of united airlines the stock 
continued to roar along on news uniteds pilots union joined by 
management and british airways plc were formulating a bid for ual 
leaving the ownership question up in the air 
ual trading in the 170s early in the summer flew up to around 
280 by the end of august and helped the dow jones average of 20 
transportation issues zoom to previously unseen altitudes 
the steep climb in the dow jones transportation average triggered 
buying by market technicians who decided their charts were pointing 
to future gains in stock prices 
mergers among pharmaceutical companies acting to increase 
competitive clout by joining forces attracted speculators to drug 
stocks the latest deal was revealed in late july when bristolmyers 
co said it would absorb squibb corp in an 11 billion stock swap 
the announcement encouraged buying in the sector 
the ability of stocks to scale new heights was noteworthy in that 
it occurred without much support from the bond market 
a bond rally fueled by expectations of easier credit ran out of 
energy in august once the view started spreading around financial 
markets that the economy might not need the stimulation of lower 
interest rates 
as activity wound down friday ahead of the long weekend the dow 
jones industrial average continued its advance at the close of 
business the average stood at a record 275209 up 1482 points 
from the previous session and 1973 higher than a week before 
weekly readings for other market measures showed the new york 
stock exchange composite index up 158 at a record 19637 the 
nasdaq composite index for the overthecounter market up 459 at 
47134 and the american stock exchange market value index up 278 
at 38396 
volume on the big board averaged 15149 million shares a day 
down from a daily average of 16596 the week before 
what lies ahead for the stock market depends partly on how 
investors read the economic tea leaves government reports issued 
friday suggested the economy has adequate pep to sustain a moderate 
expansion and the threat of a recession something economists were 
worried about earlier this summer is very remote 
regardless of what the economy does though forecasters seem to 
agree that the stock market is due for a period of consolidation 
it was really a pretty spectacular month said hugh johnson 
economist at first albany corp i dont look for anything near the 
august gains in september common sense says we have to have a 
breather 
</TEXT>
